  "Represents a range of meaning": [
   {
    "text": "A shoresh represents a broad category of meaning, like \"holiness\" for קדש, or \"death\" for מת.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "Corollaries in English": [
   {
    "text": "In English, you often have a linguistic root like \"mem\" which is used to produce a series of related words like \"memory,\" \"memorize,\" or \"memorable.\" Shorushim are a similar concept, except they are a bit more formal than in English, because there are fixed rules for how many letters they can be, and how they get turned into words.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
